<paragraph blockId="24.[93,620,213,1759]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">
DIAGNOSIS: 
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[274,391,330,353]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[274,391,330,353]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[412,528,331,352]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is distinguished from other genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KRAEPELIN" authorityYear="1905" box="[478,619,360,382]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Syntropinae">Syntropinae</taxonomicName>
by the smooth dl carinae on metasomal segments I–IV. The carinae and intercarinal surfaces of the carapace (fig. 16A), pedipalp chela, patella, tergites, metasoma, and telson (fig. 28A) are smooth in this genus. Counts of macrosetae on the carinae of metasomal segments I–IV are also greatly reduced, as follows: dl, 0/0:0/0:0/0:1/1:4/4; lm, 0/0:0/0:0/ 0:0/0:2/2; vl and vsm, 1/1:1/1:1/1:1/1:3/3. Two or more macrosetae are present on these carinae in all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KRAEPELIN" authorityYear="1905" box="[348,493,681,703]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Syntropinae">Syntropinae</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[93,207,710,733]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[93,207,710,733]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which also presents low setal counts, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pocock, 1989)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1989" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristimanus">
<emphasis box="[249,505,739,762]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Thorellius cristimanus</emphasis>
(Pocock, 1989)
</taxonomicName>
with the following counts on segments I– V: dl, 2/2:3/3:3/3:3/3:7/6; lm, 1/1:3/3:3/3:4/4:4/4; vl, 2/2:3/3:3/3:3/3:7/7; vsm, 3/3:3/3:3/3:3/3:5/5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[93,620,213,1759]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[122,239,857,880]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[122,239,857,880]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[269,394,858,879]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[225,339,886,909]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[225,339,886,909]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 7), with which it shares broad pedipalpal and metasomal carinae and, with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thorell, 1867)" baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intrepidus">
<emphasis box="[302,534,944,967]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Thorellius intrepidus</emphasis>
(Thorell, 1867)
</taxonomicName>
, double basal prolateral denticles on the movable finger of the pedipalp chela (fig. 20A, B). However, all carinae are smooth in 
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[121,238,1061,1084]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[121,238,1061,1084]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[251,359,1063,1084]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, instead of moderately to densely granular, as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[436,550,1091,1114]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[436,550,1091,1114]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The distinct proximal gap, evident when the pedipalp chela fingers are closed, in both sexes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[123,237,1178,1201]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[123,237,1178,1201]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[384,501,1178,1201]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[384,501,1178,1201]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[514,619,1179,1200]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The two genera also differ in base coloration and infuscation. 
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[312,429,1237,1260]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[312,429,1237,1260]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[456,577,1238,1259]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is yellowish and almost immaculate, except for the ocular tubercle, which is outlined by dark infuscation, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[355,469,1324,1347]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[355,469,1324,1347]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tend to be darker and reddish in color, with various degrees of infuscation on the carapace and tergites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[93,620,213,1759]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[122,239,1442,1465]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[122,239,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[259,373,1443,1464]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Mesomexovis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Mesomexovis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[182,307,1473,1494]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in possessing obsolete ventral carinae on metasomal segments I– IV, but species of the latter genus differ in being more setose and infuscate.
</paragraph>
