<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="24" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="24.[667,1193,211,1438]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">
NATURAL HISTORY: 
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[946,1063,212,235]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[946,1063,212,235]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1078,1188,213,234]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, inhabits tropical deciduous forest at altitudes between 
<quantity box="[780,920,271,293]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.335" metricValueMax="6.72" metricValueMin="1.95" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" unit="m" value="433.5" valueMax="672.0" valueMin="195.0">
195– 
<specimenCount box="[833,920,271,293]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" type="generic">672 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Specimens were observed at night, doorkeeping at the entrances of their burrows in open, sandy areas, and excavated from the burrows (
<bibRefCitation author="Ponce-Saavedra, J. &amp; W. D. Sissom" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" pagination="539 - 544" refId="ref38517" refString="Ponce-Saavedra, J., and W. D. Sissom. 2004. A new species of the genus Vaejovis (Scorpiones, Vaejovidae) endemic to the Balsas basin of Michoacan, Mexico. Journal of Arachnology 32: 539 - 544." type="journal article" year="2004">Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom, 2004</bibRefCitation>
). The glabrous integument and burrowing biology in sandy habitats suggest that this species is psammophilous although the leg setation is atypical for the psammophilous ecomorphotype, because the dorsal and retrolateral dorsal macrosetae are arranged into two separate rows, not forming a setal comb. This monotypic genus was collected at the same locality as another monotypic syntropine genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francke and Ponce-Saavedra" authorityYear="2010" box="[1034,1132,653,674]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Kuarapu" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1034,1132,653,674]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Kuarapu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although sympatric, these genera are allotopic: 
<taxonomicName authority="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini, 2013" authorityName="González-Santillán &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[667,784,710,733]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[667,784,710,733]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[802,914,711,732]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, was collected in open, sandy areas, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Francke and Ponce-Saavedra" authorityYear="2010" box="[928,1027,740,761]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Kuarapu" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[928,1027,740,761]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Kuarapu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected on road-cuts, suggesting a lithophilous ecomorphotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[667,1193,211,1438]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">
REMARKS: Due to the unique morphology of this species, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ponce-Saavedra, J. &amp; W. D. Sissom" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" pagination="539 - 544" refId="ref38517" refString="Ponce-Saavedra, J., and W. D. Sissom. 2004. A new species of the genus Vaejovis (Scorpiones, Vaejovidae) endemic to the Balsas basin of Michoacan, Mexico. Journal of Arachnology 32: 539 - 544." type="journal article" year="2004">Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom (2004)</bibRefCitation>
refrained from assigning it to one of the five species groups of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[927,1023,917,938]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,1023,917,938]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Vaejovis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recognized at the time. 
<bibRefCitation author="Soleglad, M. E. &amp; V. Fet" box="[778,1058,946,968]" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 115" refId="ref39584" refString="Soleglad, M. E., and V. Fet. 2008. Contributions to scorpion systematics. III. Subfamilies Smeringurinae and Syntropinae (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae). Euscorpius 71: 1 - 115." type="journal article" year="2008">Soleglad and Fet (2008)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[737,851,974,997]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[737,851,974,997]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a name devised for 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffmann, C. C." pageId="24" pageNumber="24" pagination="291 - 408" refId="ref37778" refString="Hoffmann, C. C. 1931. Monografias para la entomologia medica de Mexico. Monografia Num. 2, Los escorpiones de Mexico. Primera parte: Diplocentridae, Chactidae, Vaejovidae. Anales del Instituto de Biologia Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico 2: 291 - 408." type="journal article" year="1931">Hoffmann’s (1931)</bibRefCitation>
‘‘second section’’ of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[1090,1186,1005,1026]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1090,1186,1005,1026]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">Vaejovis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, later termed the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[870,981,1033,1056]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intrepidus">
<emphasis box="[870,981,1033,1056]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">intrepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sissom, W. D." pageId="24" pageNumber="24" pagination="179 - 187" refId="ref39026" refString="Sissom, W. D. 1989. Redescription of Vaejovis occidentalis Hoffmann with a revised diagnosis for Vaejovis subcristatus Pocock (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae). Revue Arachnologique 8: 179 - 187." type="journal article" year="1989">Sissom (1989)</bibRefCitation>
, without quantitatively testing its monophyly or composition. 
<bibRefCitation author="Santibanez-Lopez, C. &amp; W. D. Sissom" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" pagination="49 - 58" refId="ref38931" refString="Santibanez-Lopez, C., and W. D. Sissom. 2010. A new species of the Vaejovis eusthenura group in Oaxaca, Mexico (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae). Zootaxa 2493: 49 - 58." type="journal article" year="2010">Santibáñez-López and Sissom (2010)</bibRefCitation>
also referred this species to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[667,778,1150,1173]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="24" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intrepidus">
<emphasis box="[667,778,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="24">intrepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The creation of a monotypic genus is merited by the unique diagnostic character combination of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
